    {
      "id": "legend",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "# request-flow canvas\n\nFour columns = four real request shapes that hit the running `arc-guard-service`. Each column lists **every class on the call path** in execution order, top-to-bottom. Color key:\n\n- **cyan (5)** — pipeline / SDK contracts (always-on path)  ·  **purple (6)** — inspectors & strategies  ·  **green (4)** — pass-path stages\n- **red (1)** — block / refusal path  ·  **orange (2)** — observability sinks (some wired, some inert)  ·  **gray (no color)** — pipeline collaborators created but inert for this run\n- **yellow (3)** — schemas, settings, and configuration  ·  **GAP** boxes call out where a sink is inert / payload is dropped / inspector-level data is unobserved",
      "x": -240,
      "y": -1280,
      "width": 2740,
      "height": 293,
      "color": "3"
    },
    {
      "id": "u1_title",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "# Use case 1 — BENIGN chat\n`POST /v1/chat/completions` · backend=echo · pre=pass · post=pass",
