    {
      "id": "u4_gap_postproc",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "⚠ GAP vs chat-completions\n`/v1/guard` calls **only `pre_process`** — there is no post_process equivalent because there is no upstream LLM. Outbound-direction guarding is exclusive to the OpenAI transport today.",
      "x": 1607,
      "y": 2328,
      "width": 485,
      "height": 170,
      "color": "1"
    },
    {
      "id": "sinks_summary",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "# Cross-flow summary — what every request shares\n\n## Wired sinks (all four use cases)\n- **LogReporter** → emits stdlib WARNING for non-clean GuardResults (audit trail, post-decision)\n- **StdlibBridgeLogger** → 13–18 `event=...` lines per pipeline run on the `arc-guard.sdk` logger (per-stage timing, jailbreak detection, fidelity scoring sentinels, decision lifecycle)\n\n## Inert sinks — present, doing nothing\n- **NullMetricSink** — no `arc_guard.requests.total`, `arc_guard.findings.count`, `arc_guard.stage.duration` series. To add: implement `MetricSink`, pass `metrics_hook=` to `GuardPipeline`. Cheapest concrete impl: in-memory counters exposed at `GET /metrics` in Prometheus text format.\n- **NullTracer** — no spans, so no flame graphs and no OTEL collector correlation. To add: implement `Tracer`, pass `tracer_hook=`. The `[otel]` extra ships `OtelTracer` + `OtelLogger` + `OtelMetricSink` already; just an install + wire-up.\n\n## Architectural gaps surfaced by the canvas\n1. **Payload not captured** — sinks see sizes, never text. A dashboard cannot show before/after diffs without a new sink type that opts into payload capture (with redaction discipline so PII doesn't leak into the audit channel).\n2. **No inspector-level timing** — `stage=classify` total is logged, but per-inspector breakdown (Injection vs Presidio) is not. Adding a per-inspector `event=guard.inspector.completed name=... duration_ms=...` would need a Logger Protocol enhancement inside `_run_inspector_chain`.\n3. **No outbound rehydration** — sanitized PII placeholders forwarded into the LLM stay as placeholders in the response. A `RehydrationVerifier` impl + `post_process` rewrite step would close this.\n4. **No abuse signal aggregation** — repeated blocks from one `x-request-id` source aren't counted or rate-limited. Belongs in api-layer middleware, not the pipeline.\n5. **post_process is OpenAI-transport-only** — `/v1/guard` callers never get outbound guarding. If a future `/v1/responses` (Anthropic-style) transport lands, it'll need to mirror the openai router's pre+post pattern.",
      "x": -240,
      "y": 4394,
      "width": 2740,
      "height": 586,
      "color": "3"
    }
